Michael P. Gianoni  Chief Executive Officer, President and Non-Independent Director, Blackbaud, Inc.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 3 Board Members in 3 different organizations across 6 different industries.See Board Relationships56$5,709,266As of Fiscal Year 2016
Background

		Mr. Michael P. Gianoni, also known as Mike, has been the Chief Executive Officer and President of Blackbaud Inc. since January 13, 2014. Mr. Gianoni oversees strategic direction of Blackbaud Inc. He served as an Executive Vice President and the Group President of Financial Institutions Group at Fiserv, Inc. since January 2010. He was responsible for Digital Channels (Online Banking and Mobile Banking), Investment Services, Lending Services, Risk Management Solutions, ... Consulting and Output Solutions at Fiserv Inc. He served as President of Investment Services at Fiserv from 2007 to 2009 and was responsible for product, technology, sales, finance, operations and strategy. He served as an Executive Vice President of CheckFree Corporation from June 2006 to 2007. He has more than 25 years of diverse business experience in the e-commerce, software and computer manufacturing industries. He served as the President of Checkfree Investment Services, Inc. He served as Executive Vice President and General Manager of CheckFree Investment Services Inc. from 2005 to 2007 and also at CheckFree Services Corporation since June 2006. From 1994 to 2005, he served as Senior Vice President of DST Systems, Inc. He served as Senior Vicne President of E-Solutions of Dst Output Inc. from 2004 to June 2006. From 2001 to 2004, he served as the Senior Vice President of Client Services & Systems at DST Systems, Inc. He served at DST Systems for 11 years and led the National Client Services & Systems organization. Mr. Gianoni has held management positions in engineering, systems development and sales throughout his 20-year career. He served in a variety of executive leadership roles with Application Systems Group, Sequent Computer Systems, Wang Laboratories, U.S. Design Corporation and Canberra Industries. He has been a Director of Teradata Corporation since January 27, 2015 and Blackbaud Inc. since January 13, 2014. He serves as a Member of Advisory Board of LifeYield, LLC. Mr. Gianoni received his associate degree in electrical engineering at Waterbury State Technical College and bachelor's degree with a business concentration from Charter Oak State College. He holds a Master Degree in Business Administration from the University of New Haven.Read Full Background




